-- Guess second-quarter profit leaps
-- 
-- Tue Sep 4, 2007 4:22pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/04/us-guess-results-idUSWNAS335220070904

 

 (Reuters) - Guess? Inc ( GES.N ), which makes clothing and accessories and has its own stores, posted a 81.5 percent increase in quarterly profit as all its businesses delivered double digit revenue increases. 

 The Los Angeles-based company reported second-quarter net income of $37.5 million, or 40 cents a share, compared with $20.6 million, or 22 cents a share, a year earlier. Total net revenue increased more than 48 percent to $388.3 million. Analysts on average expected earnings of 33 cents a share, before exceptional items, on revenue of $345.6 million, according to Reuters Estimates. (Reporting by Aditi Samajpati in Bangalore)